    <text id="F8023T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Berryhill writes in support of a clerkship assignment for the son of D. O.
                Gehr.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
             

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-11-12"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 12th.
                        1860</date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Honorable">Honr.</abbr> Simon Cameron<lb/>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>By the request of D O. Gehr <abbr expan="Esquire">Esq</abbr> I am induced, again,
                    to claim, your friendship and interposition in behalf of his Son, Hastings, who
                    has been recently admitted to practice Law in this place but as he is not an
                    orator, &amp; as it will require much time and study, to become celebrated
                    in his profession, he inclines to a Clerkship at Harrisburg or Washington City.</p>
                <p>I will say he is smart, writes a good hand and by a little experience will become
                    a good accountant is moral, Steady, and amiable, and would prove a creditable
                    acquisition in any position he may be called to act. Your attention to him will
                    much oblige Your old friend and <abbr expan="Obedient">Obt.</abbr> Servant</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">John Berryhill</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
